The paper deals with the complexity of enumerating the answers of Conjunctive Queries (CQs) in the presence of Functional Dependencies (FDs), which are fundamental concepts in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity theory, which are covered by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The authors use linear-time preprocessing and discuss the enumeration delay, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper deals with the generalization of FDs, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
